&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;Nothing that has been said so far explains why chance is obedient to laws... our frailty does not permit us to take in the whole universe, but forces us to cut it up in slices.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt; - Henri Poincaré, 1903&lt;/p&gt;
